product_name: LancomeTeint Idole Ultra Wear All Over Concealer
summary: SummaryLanc√¥me Teint Idole Ultra Wear All Over Concealer is a hydrating, lightweight, full coverage concealer that brightens dark under eyes and covers imperfections¬†without creasing or caking.
details: DetailsFeaturesInfused with skin-loving ingredients, this multi-use¬†concealer provides up to 24H of hydration and comfort in matte finish for a natural makeup look.The ultra-blendable makeup formula and precise tip applicator target¬†dark spots, blemishes, and redness¬†without settling into fine lines or creasing.This dark circles concealer can be worn on its own or together with Teint Idole Ultra Wear 24H Longwear foundation.All-In-1 usage to conceal, highlight, correct, and contour.BenefitsWeightless full coverageUltra-blendableComfortable wearSuitable for sensitive skinNatural matte finishNo creasing or cakingSweat-resistantUp to 24H hydrationAll-in-1 usageNon-comedogenicTested under dermatological controlItem 2583109How To UseAll-In-1 Usage:Conceal & Highlight: Apply as an under eye concealer to brighten dark circles; Apply on the forehead, down the nose, and on the cupid's bow and chin to highlight the high points of the face. Choose a shade lighter than your base skin tone.Correct: Apply as a dark spot concealer directly on to blemishes, dark spots, and redness to even skin tone. Tap with finger to seamlessly blend. Choose a shade that matches your base skin tone.Contour: Apply on the forehead, sides of the nose, cheek bones and jaw line to sculpt your face. Choose a shade 2-3 shades deeper than your base skin tone.IngredientsAqua / Water, Undecane, Dimethicone, Glycerin, Tridecane, Polyglyceryl-4 Isostearate, Pentylene Glycol, Cetyl PEG/PPG-10/1 Dimethicone, Hexyl Laurate, Magnesium Sulfate, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Rosa Gallica Flower Extract, Helianthus Annuus Seed Oil / Sunflower Seed Oil, Moringa Oleifera Seed Extract, Nymphaea Alba Flower Extract, Isobutane, Sorbitol, Trihydroxystearin, Cellulose Gum, Aluminum Hydroxide, Disodium Phosphate, Disodium Stearoyl Glutamate, Propanediol, Propylene Glycol, Citric Acid, Acetylated Glycol Stearate, Ethylhexylglycerin, Acrylonitrile/Methyl Methacrylate/Vinylidene Chloride Copolymer, Tocopherol, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, Phenoxyethanol.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.headline: Too dry to use under eyes
reviews.comments: I am age 56 - many concealers accent my under-eye wrinkles and bags, and this one is no exception.  Older ladies, you want the Lancome Ultra Wear Care & Glow serum concealer - that's one of the best ones out there. Steer clear of this one for eyes.

reviews.headline: Bring back Effacernes or make a new waterproof concealer!
reviews.comments:
Very happy with Ulta, incredibly angry with Lanc√¥me for discontinuing Effacernes waterproof concealer. This concealer doesn't cover as well and by the end of the day it runs and looks chalky because it's not waterproof. Ugh! 
Why has Lanc√¥me been discontinuing so many of its favorites.

reviews.headline: A new fave!
reviews.comments: The best concealer for my undereyes that I have come across. Great coverage and I don't feel like I have anything on my skin.

reviews.headline: Perfect coverage
reviews.comments: I have bought this several times, it covers and doesn't enhance my fine lines under my eyes.

reviews.headline: Best concealer I've ever tried
reviews.comments: This is the best concealer I've ever used. I seriously love it so much because it has the best coverage and blends even when my skin is a little peely from using retinol! Please do not ever discontinue it!

reviews.headline: Great concealer
reviews.comments: I love this concealer!  It covers my dark circles without looking caked on.

reviews.headline: BEST CONCEALER I'VE USED
reviews.comments: This concealer is NOT drying, its full coverage and does not feel heavy. It blends so well and lasts all day.  I have combination skin where I tend to get oily in my t-zone but have dry under eyes. This concealer has been a game changer! 10/10!!!

reviews.headline: Shade 335 Bisque (c)
reviews.comments:
Why is it pink? Legitimate question... I saw the good reviews and I gave in to it.... 
Bought it online and even used the shade finder. When I swatched it on my neck it was way darker and with a BIG pink undertone to it. Not a shade with a cooler undertone like the description said, wich it sucks because first impression of the formula itself was great (taking aside the smell of it). 

The doe-foot applicator it's so angled that everytime you try to get product it kinda splooshes? It's not as bad as other packagings, not too messy, but still messy. I guess that mkre kd a personal preference thing...

I'm not even sure if I can return it, since it was opened and swatched. I'll still try to because the shade range it's so off I can't even make it work. 

 Also, the smell was something like house paint? Not sure how to describe it, it's a very chemicall-y smell but not too strong tho. 

Overall not bad, not great, shade range need some expansion..

reviews.headline: Ive continude to purchase this product.
reviews.comments: I dont like to wear much make up and I am over 40, So I dont want a cakey face. This is perfectly light yet provides good coverage. My only complaint is it is too small, last me only about 4 months.

reviews.headline: Yes, I would buy this under eye concealer again.
reviews.comments: Does not completely cover dark circles but is moisturizing and natural looking.

reviews.headline: My staple
reviews.comments: I have had trouble in the past finding a concealer that doesnt make me look washed out  or just doesn't sit right on my face. I really like this one because it blends so nicely into the skin and has the perfect amount of coverage for under the eyes.

reviews.headline: LOVED IT!!!!
reviews.comments: I LOVED IT - MATCHED PERFECTLY

reviews.headline: Amazing
reviews.comments: I got the shade 090/Ivory N, and it matched me good! I'm more on the pale-cool tone side so i always have a difficult time finding good matches but this was a good fit (it does oxideze as well, but it is not very noticeable.) It has good coverage, it's not too thick, but I will say it does crease under the eyes after a while (but that always happens to me, so I believe with a good base, it might not.) I can't really say how well it does with blending since I use small amounts, but it does seem like it blends pretty well. I would say I have combination skin so i have trouble finding concealers that work but this one worked great for me. I would definitely recommend this and will for sure buy it again because it is worth the price!

reviews.headline: Had High Hopes‚Ä¶
reviews.comments: I love Lancome products and was so excited to try this as all the good reviews raved about it. The overall consistency blends nicely and lightweight but the shade range is sadly lacking. Im a medium complexion and to get any sort of brightening effect i had to buy the lightest shade possible. And when you open the tube it flicks concealer everywhere! I wont be repurchasing and don't recommend, better out there especially for the price!

reviews.headline: Nearly perfect
reviews.comments: Great coverage. Blends beautifully. My only complaint is that the applicator doesn't always come out of the tube smoothly. On more than one occasion the doe foot gets a little jammed and causes some of the product to burst out from the packaging. Thank goodness the spots have been easily removable from my clothes.

reviews.headline: My Go-To Undereye Concealer
reviews.comments: Love how natural this looks~ likely bc you don't need a lot to get the coverage you need.  With a primer and a setting spray, I'm able to get it to look nice all day.

reviews.headline: Yes

reviews.headline: Glittery!
reviews.comments: I don't know why the reviews don't mention this, but this product has micro-glitters/shimmer particles in it. I am super bummed because the formula, shade range, and packaging are all really nice. Unfortunately this will he a return for me.

faceoff_positive.comments: When I don't feel the need for a full face foundation, this is my go to to even out skin tone, conceal dark circles, etc. A little goes a long way. It does not emphasize or settle into fine lines. I do use a light setting powder and it lasts all day.
faceoff_positive.headline: Performs beautifully on mature skin.

faceoff_negative.comments: This is absolutely Terrible!  I beg you to bring back Maquicomplet.  Not only was the formula better, especially for those of us over 55 and beyond, but Clair II was the absolute most perfect shade match that I've ever found. And now I don't know what to use.  I purchased this this Teint Idole and it's too dry, it looks cakey even though I make sure my under eye is well hydrated. I've tried three other high end concealers trying to find a suitable replacement and my old, nearly empty Maquicomplet is still the winner by far!  Also the Teint Idole color that is "supposed " to be equivalent to Clair II is not even close.  I was told two different color matches, one online and one in store where I purchased.  Just please bring back Clair II in Maquicomplet!  The formula was lightweight and natural looking, I miss it terribly.
faceoff_negative.headline: This is NOT a replacement for Maquicomplet
